Today in America, family income still plays an outsized role in determining a student's likelihood of going to a top college, and far too many high-achieving students, especially from low- and middle-income families, are missing out on opportunities to attend schools that match their abilities.

@princetonebc raises the bar for what college access and success should mean through its support of first-generation college students, veterans, students transferring from community colleges, and enrolling more students from lower-income families.

Not only will the Center advance @princeton’s commitment to an inclusive student body, but it will also expand educational access by serving as a hub for research and innovation for other institutions committed to increasing socioeconomic diversity on college campuses.

As mayor, I worked with President Bush, Governor Pataki & Governor Paterson to acquire @governorsisland and proposed transforming it into a park and campus, which would bring new life & jobs to New York City. 

My administration opened a public school on the island and began building a public park - and now, thanks to @NYCMayor's leadership, our vision is being further realized with the unveiling of the New York Climate Exchange. Led by Mayor Eric Adams, the Trust for Governors Island, and @StonyBrookU, the 400,000 square foot campus will focus on developing and deploying solutions to the climate crisis. 

@BloombergDotOrg is glad to join the Simons Foundation in support of the New York Climate Exchange, which will also bring education and job opportunities to NYC. Learn more at the link in my bio.

